<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 1:32PM CDT  by NWS Little Rock</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Saline and
northeastern Hot Spring Counties through 200 PM CDT...
At 132 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Rockport, or near Malvern, moving east at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Malvern...                        Rockport...
Traskwood...                      Perla...
Magnet Cove...                    Gifford...
Glen Rose...                      Lake Catherine State Park...
This includes Interstate 30 between mile markers 93 and 108.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
